snippet.title: Taara Taara - Lyrical| HariHaraVeeraMallu |PSPK| Nidhhi | MM Keeravaani | AM Rathnam| Jyothi Krisna
snippet.description:
The ultimate dance dhamaka is here! üíÉüï∫Vibe to 'Taara Taara' from Hari Hara Veera Mallu and let the beats take over! üé∂Featuring PSPK and Nidhhi Agerwal, this track is composed by Oscar-winning MM Keeravani and directed by Jyothi Krisna & Krish Jagarlamudi. 

Stay updated with the latest videos from Tips Telugu, Subscribe on the below link
https://youtube.com/TipsTelugu

Song Details -  
Song Name: Taara Taara
Music Director:  M. M. Keeravaani
Lyricist: Sri Harsha Emani 
Rap lyrics : Aditya Iyengar
Singers: Lipsika Bhashyam, Aditya Iyengar
Additional Vocals: Arun Kaundinya, Lokeshwar Edara.
Programmed by: Bharath Madhusudanan  
Additional Programming: G Jeevan Babu 
Guitalele: Jeevan Babu

Lyrics 
Male Chorus :
Pothunte Nuvvala Ala
Bazaar Mottham Goley Gola
Kopamga Nuv Choododdala 
Pelaboye Firangila‚Ä¶!
Em Kaavaloy Pilla
Merusthunnav Thalaa Thalaa..
Entho Cheppu Thamari Vela 
Mohareela? Varahaala?

Pallavi : (Heroine)
Taara Taara Naa Kallu 
Vennela Pootha Naa Ollu 
Aakasanni Enthakani
Vela Kadathaaru‚Ä¶!
Taara Taara Naa Kallu 
Vennela Pootha Naa Ollu 
Aakasanni Enthakani
Vela Kadathaaru‚Ä¶!

Charanam : (Heroine)
Chemata Chukka Paditey 
Vajramanukuntaaru‚Ä¶!
Vaddhaku Vacchi Nilabaditey 
Thadabadathaaru‚Ä¶!
Ballem Baanam Kante 
Nadumu Padhunaindoyi..
Kavachamunna Gundekainaa
Gaayaalavthaayi‚Ä¶!
Pedavi Kosam Padavulu 
Naabhiki Naalugu Oollu 
Arpisthaamantunnaaru 
Ee Nawaabulu‚Ä¶!

Taara Taara Naa Kallu 
Vennela Pootha Naa Vollu 
Aakasanni Enthakani 
Vela Kadathaaru‚Ä¶!

Male Chorus :
Kanti Choopuloni Nigha
Panti Kinda Pedavi Sega 
Sogasula Sirulu Bhaga
Rammani Cheppaka Chebuthundaga 
Kaatu Veyi Okkotiga 
Reguthondi Vayasu Thega 
Ghaatuga Unnadi Poga 
Raguluthondi Bhaga Bhaga‚Ä¶!

Charanam : (Heroine)
Kallu Ollu Kaadabba 
Mohabbat Ka Jazba 
Velam Vesi Daanni Evaru Konalerabba‚Ä¶!
Aasha Maashi Kaadabba 
Ee Kanne Shobha‚Ä¶
Vela Kanna Viluva Thelisinodenabba‚Ä¶!

snippet.title: Uppum Mulakum 3 | Flowers | EP # 307
snippet.description:
'Uppum Mulakum' returns with its third season, continuing as one of Malayalam TV's longest-running sitcoms. This beloved show blends humor and emotion, depicting the trials and tribulations of a middle-class family. Balachandran and his family are back in action. Let's see what's next!!

Sise ki meri jawani
Mai hu pari Aasmani
Aankhe Gulabi Gulabi

Lakho diwana Mare Rojana 
Dil Hola Bekarar 
Aaela Jab Chal Ke 

Karela Bawal Tohar Ghaghara Jalidar 
Dupatta Mal Mal Ke

Ho Jaye Da Pyar

Kabo Halke Halke

Dupatta Mal Mal Ke

Aag Lage style Par 
Hola Murder Smile Par

Mohabat Ba Bhar Bhar Ke

Odhaniya Sar Sarke

Dekhela Tab Tab 
Penhila Jab Jab 
Hathawa Me Chatkar 
Chudi Lalke Lalke

Gora Gora Face Pa 
Gori Kala Kala Bal 
Lipistik Purple Ke

80 Ke Raftar 
Kabo Halke Halke

Chauraha Kabo Gali pa
Aawe Bhaura eh Kali Pa

Umariya Nanhki Nanhki
Satelu Tanki Tanki 
Marat Balu Kankhi Kankhi 
Ta Manawa Sanaki Sanki 

Sahal Na Jala nahi Sohala 
Hamara Ke Bewahar Aashu Neelkamal Ke 

Jab Se Tohake Dekhale Bani 
Chadhata Bukhar 
Jarurat Ba Phal Ke 

Karela Bawal Tohar Ghaghara Jalidar 
Dupatta Mal Mal Ke

snippet.description:
Click here to subscribe to the Sony LIV Channel: 
https://www.youtube.com/user/sonyliv

Everyone argues over the unaddressed tempo in the Gokuldham Society. Bapuji intervenes and asks them to come up with a solution rather than arguing with each other. Jethalal has a heartfelt conversation with his grandfather. Later, he revisits memories of the Republic Day celebration and decides to call Babitaji to appreciate Mahila Mandal's efforts for the preparations. Jethalal reads the letter to Babitaji that she found in Iyer's book. It was a love letter that he translates completely for Babitaji. Later, Jethalal's fear comes true, when Sundar arrives at his home and starts dancing.

Show Name - Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast - Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt
Produced By - Asit Kumar Modi, Neela Asit Modi

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in 'Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The residents of the housing society, help each other find solutions when they face common, real-life challenges and get involved in sticky situations.

Besides the design changes both inside and out, Tata claims to have worked on the suspension setup and the chassis (reinforcements - details of which will be discussed in the review video.

snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun.

#GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame

Watch the FULL MOVIE of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSk2_rPKNCDcjNAA8vaDN-E&si=rC5AotwLD2r3MHna

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Jheel Mehta / Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal / Monaz Mevawalla as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah / Dharmit Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku 
Ghanshyam Nayak / Kiran Bhatt as Nattu Kaka
Tanmay Vekaria as Bagha
Navina Wadekar / Monika Bhadoriya as Bawri

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: FRUIT MIXER | Colorful Healthy Fruits Mixed Recipe | Summer Health Fruit Recipe Making in Village
snippet.description:
Today in our village, we made a colorful and healthy fruit mixer using fresh fruits. We included apples, oranges, watermelon, strawberries, kiwis, mangoes, papayas, jackfruit, and more, along with soaked almond gum, basil seeds, and pure honey for added taste and health benefits.

The video beautifully cuts and shows all the fruits, making it refreshing and satisfying to watch. This natural recipe is perfect for all seasons, especially summer, and is a great healthy fruit recipe for kids.

id.description:

snippet.title: The mind of a Genius: Kamal Haasan on Art, life and passion | Gobinath
snippet.description:
Enquiries:
talk2gobinath@gmail.com

#Gobinath #kamalhaasan #ulaganayagan #art #life #passion #legacy #podcast #cinema #tamilcinema #legacyofexcellence 

Stay ahead with direct updates from Gobinath ‚Äî interviews, insights, and powerful voices.
Join the official WhatsApp Channel today:
https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Vb5gNn82Jl8DSfwhUM3G

In this powerful episode, Gobinath sits down with the legendary Ulaganayagan Kamal Haasan‚Äîa visionary who has not just acted in cinema but revolutionized it. 

With fearless creativity, deep philosophy, and decades of reinvention, Kamal reflects on a life lived in service of art. From listening to the heart over algorithms to exploring aging, AI, acting, and mortality, this conversation dives into the mind of a master.

From listening to the heart over algorithms to exploring aging, AI, and the ethics of cinema, Kamal opens up about:

 ‚Ä¢ His constant reinvention and evolution as an artist
 ‚Ä¢ The humbling moments that shaped his self-awareness
 ‚Ä¢ Learning from the ancients, yet daring to innovate
 ‚Ä¢ Acting not as imitation but as raw, requested ‚Äúmisbehavior‚Äù
 ‚Ä¢ Balancing perfection with beautiful imperfection
 ‚Ä¢ Time, discipline, mortality‚Äîand the pursuit of artistic immortality
 ‚Ä¢ The philosophies behind his cinema: for whom, and why
 ‚Ä¢ The tension between market demands and meaningful messaging
 ‚Ä¢ Minimalism, nostalgia, and the emotional universality of war and motherhood
 ‚Ä¢ His Gandhian turn and his deeply underrated contributions as a lyricist
 ‚Ä¢ Tamil‚Äôs rhythmic beauty and its global poetic power
 ‚Ä¢ The role of cinema in shaping society and the next generation
 ‚Ä¢ Corporate capitalism, global politics, and center-aligned balance
 ‚Ä¢ Parenting, emotional intelligence, and legacy beyond screens
 ‚Ä¢ His take on AI, knowledge, and the evolving boundaries of intelligence
 ‚Ä¢ The behind-the-scenes genius of the technicians behind Thug Life
 ‚Ä¢ And his reflections on the title Thug Life and its connection to Nayakan

Kamal also shares heartfelt memories from his childhood, honors icons like Sivaji, Kannadasan, Periyar, and Kalaignar, and lays bare what continues to drive his tireless journey as a creator.

This episode is more than an interview‚Äîit‚Äôs a philosophical masterclass, a celebration of art, and a tribute to the spirit of relentless curiosity.

A must-watch for cinephiles, thinkers, artists, and dreamers who believe in the power of storytelling to change the world.

localized.description:
Enquiries:
talk2gobinath@gmail.com

#Gobinath #kamalhaasan #ulaganayagan #art #life #passion #legacy #podcast #cinema #tamilcinema #legacyofexcellence 

Stay ahead with direct updates from Gobinath ‚Äî interviews, insights, and powerful voices.
Join the official WhatsApp Channel today:
https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Vb5gNn82Jl8DSfwhUM3G

In this powerful episode, Gobinath sits down with the legendary Ulaganayagan Kamal Haasan‚Äîa visionary who has not just acted in cinema but revolutionized it. 

With fearless creativity, deep philosophy, and decades of reinvention, Kamal reflects on a life lived in service of art. From listening to the heart over algorithms to exploring aging, AI, acting, and mortality, this conversation dives into the mind of a master.

From listening to the heart over algorithms to exploring aging, AI, and the ethics of cinema, Kamal opens up about:

 ‚Ä¢ His constant reinvention and evolution as an artist
 ‚Ä¢ The humbling moments that shaped his self-awareness
 ‚Ä¢ Learning from the ancients, yet daring to innovate
 ‚Ä¢ Acting not as imitation but as raw, requested ‚Äúmisbehavior‚Äù
 ‚Ä¢ Balancing perfection with beautiful imperfection
 ‚Ä¢ Time, discipline, mortality‚Äîand the pursuit of artistic immortality
 ‚Ä¢ The philosophies behind his cinema: for whom, and why
 ‚Ä¢ The tension between market demands and meaningful messaging
 ‚Ä¢ Minimalism, nostalgia, and the emotional universality of war and motherhood
 ‚Ä¢ His Gandhian turn and his deeply underrated contributions as a lyricist
 ‚Ä¢ Tamil‚Äôs rhythmic beauty and its global poetic power
 ‚Ä¢ The role of cinema in shaping society and the next generation
 ‚Ä¢ Corporate capitalism, global politics, and center-aligned balance
 ‚Ä¢ Parenting, emotional intelligence, and legacy beyond screens
 ‚Ä¢ His take on AI, knowledge, and the evolving boundaries of intelligence
 ‚Ä¢ The behind-the-scenes genius of the technicians behind Thug Life
 ‚Ä¢ And his reflections on the title Thug Life and its connection to Nayakan

Kamal also shares heartfelt memories from his childhood, honors icons like Sivaji, Kannadasan, Periyar, and Kalaignar, and lays bare what continues to drive his tireless journey as a creator.

This episode is more than an interview‚Äîit‚Äôs a philosophical masterclass, a celebration of art, and a tribute to the spirit of relentless curiosity.

A must-watch for cinephiles, thinkers, artists, and dreamers who believe in the power of storytelling to change the world.

snippet.title: Housefull 5 Trailer REVIEW | Deeksha Sharma
snippet.description:
Housefull 5 Trailer Review By Deeksha Sharma. Akshay Kumar Comeback in Comedy with Housefull 5 Franchise is all set for Box Office Surprise after Mystery Thriller Twist & Turns in a Family Comedy Cinema. Housefull 5 Trailer is big on Jokes but Short on Suspense supported by a Larger than life Supporting Cast.

Starring :  
Akshay Kumar, Abhishek A Bachchan, Riteish Deshmukh, Jacqueline Fernandez, Sonam Bajwa, Nargis Fakhri, Sanjay Dutt, Jackie Shroff, Nana Patekar, Chitrangada Singh, Fardeen Khan, Chunky Pandey, Johnny Lever, Shreyas Talpade, Dino Morea, Ranjeet, Soundarya Sharma, Nikitin Dheer, and Akashdeep Sabir 

Housefull 5 Trailer Review Reaction & Full Movie Expectations would be shared in this Video. Can Akshay Kumar score another Hit for Bollywood or Comedy Thriller might get overshadowed due to high expectations? Do leave your Comments below.

snippet.title: Bhide aur Jethalal ki Ladai! | FULL MOVIE | Part 1 | Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Watch the FULL MOVIE of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSk2_rPKNCDcjNAA8vaDN-E&si=rC5AotwLD2r3MHna

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Jheel Mehta / Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal / Monaz Mevawalla as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah / Dharmit Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku 
Ghanshyam Nayak / Kiran Bhatt as Nattu Kaka
Tanmay Vekaria as Bagha
Navina Wadekar / Monika Bhadoriya as Bawri

Produced By: Neela Asit Modi, Asit Kumarr Modi 
Special Thanks: Mahesh Vakil, Indu Tarak Mehta
Set Design: Jayant Deshmukh
On-Air Promotion  ( SAB): SAB OAP
Costume Designer: Alka Mehta
Costume Stylist: Ekta Brahmbhatt

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Ek tarfa thi thai andhi mere pyar ne
Gediyan pe gedi maari saans na liya
Chora aya tha milan kade laal car mein
Ankhya mein leke ghane khaab aya su
Teri khatir main chori re gulab laya su
Aaj bhi yo chaale se pasand teri gel
Mere fool ke liye main poora baag laya su

Leke lamborghini tere gate pe khada

Geet sonipat aale ke tu gaati chaliye
Visa lagwa ke baat diye sare gaam mein
Team all good aale dhool thate aaliye
Bhola baba dekh chore ki support mein khadeya
Jabe teri gelya ban teri jott mein khadeya
